✅ Project 5 — Mini Shopping Cart
🧾 Summary

In this project, I built a text-based shopping cart program using Python. The program allows users to select items from a menu, keeps track of the total cost, and prints a receipt at the end.

🛒 How the cart handles duplicate items

If the same item is selected multiple times, the program does not create a new entry. Instead, it increases the quantity of that item in the cart.

Example:

First selection → Apple x1
Second selection → Apple x2

This is done using a dictionary:

if name in cart:
    cart[name] += 1
else:
    cart[name] = 1
❌ What happens with invalid input

If the user enters a number that is not in the menu (for example 6 or 0), the program:

Shows an error message: "Invalid choice. Try again."
Continues running without crashing
💡 Key Concepts Used
Dictionaries (menu and cart)
While loop (for continuous shopping)
Conditions (if / elif / else)
f-strings for formatting output
